The paper discusses the use of mathematical phylogenetics and genome-wide data sets to infer phylogenetic trees, which involves computational methods and algorithms. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Data Mining (cs.DM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with the identification and classification of genes, which could fall under the Databases (cs.DB) or Computational Biology (cs.CE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the use of gene trees to infer species trees, which involves the use of algorithms and computational methods to make inferences about evolutionary relationships, suggesting that the paper may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
